Let's create the dummy backend service and namespace first so your Ingress has somewhere to point.

kubectl create namespace rocket
kubectl create deployment rocket-server --image=nginx -n rocket
kubectl expose deployment rocket-server --port=80 -n rocket


Your Task:
Based on the exam screenshot, you need to create an Ingress resource with the following specifications:

Name: rocket-ingress

Namespace: rocket

Annotation: Enforce SSL redirection (nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/ssl-redirect: "true")

Ingress Class: nginx

Routing Rules:

Host: rocket-server.local

Path: / (Prefix)

Backend Service: rocket-server on port 80

----

k create secret tls secret-tls -n rocket --key=/var/lib/kubelet/pki/kubelet.key --cert=/var/lib/kubelet/pki/
kubelet.crt 
secret/secret-tls created

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: rocket-ingress
  namespace: rocket
  annotations:
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/ssl-redirect: "true"
spec:
  ingressClassName: nginx
  tls:
  - hosts:
      - rocket-server.local
    secretName: secret-tls
  rules:
  - host: rocket-server.local
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: rocket-server
            port:
              number: 80

kubectl get svc -n ingress-nginx
